      "is_answer_order_important": false,
      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>Which of the following alkenes would you expect to be good Diels–Alder dienophiles?</p>\n<p><b>(a)</b> <img src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBc1VVIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--a74df270e19909e88d334b83ca31894238f72c5d/OChem_14_05_014a.jpg\" alt=\"The condensed structural formula reads, H 2 C double bonded to C H C (double bonded to O) C l.\">\n <b>(b)</b> <img src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBc1lVIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--42f419c4a955c5b4841af0bc9531d6c03019241d/OChem_14_05_014b.jpg\" alt=\"The condensed structural formula reads, H 2 C double bonded to C H C H 2 C H 2 C (double bonded to O) O C H 3.\">\n <b>(c)</b><img src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBc2NVIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--6a36447e9f6d5f4b3eb63dc7a23cf42e2f47d1f7/OChem_14_05_014c.jpg\" alt=\"A cyclohexane ring has a double bond between C 1 and C 2.\">\n <b>(d)</b><img src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBc2dVIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--0334aa4064a1c77346401edf4cda9554fc537ab1/OChem_14_05_014d.jpg\" alt=\"In a cyclohexane ring, C 1 is a carbonyl group. C 2 is double bonded to C 3.\">\n <b>(e)</b><img src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBc2tVIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--c88dcf057165b81f646bd2840cedc3a8ad144c67/OChem_14_05_014e.jpg\" alt=\"In a cyclohexane ring, C 1 is a carbonyl group. C 3 is double bonded to C 4.\"></p>",
